  "text": "Trace context propagation across Go services is implemented using OpenTelemetry (otel) and Jaeger propagators. In Grafana, the central tracing infrastructure is in `pkg/infra/tracing/tracing.go`, which manages TracingService initialization with support for both Jaeger and W3C TraceContext propagators. The `Inject()` method (line 345-347) uses `otel.GetTextMapPropagator().Inject(ctx, propagation.HeaderCarrier(header))` to inject trace context into HTTP headers. Context extraction from incoming requests is handled in multiple layers: `pkg/middleware/request_tracing.go` (line 103) uses `otel.GetTextMapPropagator().Extract()` for server-side request tracing, `pkg/apiserver/endpoints/filters/jaeger_tracing.go` (line 14) specifically extracts Jaeger trace context, and `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/tracing.go` (line 19) extracts context from gRPC metadata. For outgoing requests, `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/tracing_middleware.go` (line 37) calls `tracer.Inject()` to propagate context to remote services.\n\nIn Kubernetes, trace propagation is standardized through `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/tracing/utils.go`, which defines the `Propagators()` function (lines 132-134) returning a composite propagator with W3C TraceContext and Baggage. The `WithTracing()` filter in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/traces.go` (lines 34-67) wraps HTTP handlers with `otelhttp.NewHandler()` using these propagators, automatically handling both extraction from incoming requests and injection into outgoing requests. The `WrapperFor()` function (lines 119-129) provides client-side tracing by wrapping RoundTripper instances with `otelhttp.NewTransport()`, ensuring trace context flows through to upstream services.\n\nIn Prometheus, trace management is centralized in `tracing/tracing.go` with the `Manager` type. The `Run()` method (line 62) registers the global TextMapPropagator as `propagation.TraceContext{}`. For client-side propagation, `storage/remote/client.go` wraps HTTP transports with `otelhttp.NewTransport()` for both read (line 161) and write (line 223) clients, with optional client trace instrumentation using `otelhttptrace`. The `web/web.go` file uses `otelhttp.NewHandler()` to wrap HTTP handlers with tracing support. All three projects standardize on OpenTelemetry's W3C TraceContext propagator for inter-service trace context correlation."
}

